entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: okay how are you at controlling your temper

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: i would say very good

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: when was the last time you argued with someone and what was it about

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: oh yeah that does not make it seem that good last time i argued was over someone actually spitting out a racial slur towards my wife

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: oh no how did you feel in that moment

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: angry upset hurt disrespected

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: yeah

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: and especially when i went up there to treat the person actually i was treating em with dignity and respect and trying to help the person at first

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: i am sorry to hear that

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: it is no problem people are people

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: okay tell me about your relationship with your family

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: blood family we really do not talk my wife do not know if she really wants to be there with me or not she thinks that i am doing everything in the world but that i am not and really i do not understand i know my daughter loves me but i do not know if she wants to be with me or not

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: why

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: because when somebody talks to you when they say something a certain amount of times and the tonage in they voice and the belief in their eyes if you say something so many times it is what really lies in your heart so you could say whatever through your mouth but it is what really is there

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: i see tell me about your kids

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: h i love my daughter she a angel i cut her bilical cord i went out there and put on her first shirt i seen her come out she looked at me right out the stomach she would not she was fighting with the doctors would not let em touch her a bit i talked to her i told her to calm down or i told her it was daddy she looked up at me grabbed my fingers and like just calmed down and just let em do everything they needed to do

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: aw do you find it easy to be a parent

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: no it is constantly changing task what you have to do on this day will not be the same thing as the next or the next after that it is constantly what is a better word for it adjusting

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: yeah

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: can you tell me about that

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: they basically showed me no matter where you come from you can always strive to get better

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: okay how easy is it for you to get a good night is sleep

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: a good night is sleep eh it comes

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: what are you like when you do not sleep well

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: the same just tired and yawning

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: how have you been feeling lately

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: how have i been feeling like i have a wealth of queries and a wealth of gold within my grasp and it is just right out of my reach because i just need that one connector to really just see what i am capable of and i know i am capable of a lot it is just i need to make that connection

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: h have you noticed any changes in your behavior or thoughts lately

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: no

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: have you ever been diagnosed with ptsd

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: not ptsd no

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: have you been diagnosed with depression

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: i said yes but i do not figure i am any more depressed or anything than any other person everyone has their different breaking points

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: okay tell me about the last time you felt really happy

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: my daughter is birthday on the twenty sixth

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: can you tell me about that

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: took her out to chuck e cheese she had fun she played games she was on bikes she was crawling through puzzle games man this girl did about everything
